00:24:14.310 --> 00:24:17.640 align:middle line:84%
as the 16-year-old hired the
16-year-old while they still

00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:19.290 align:middle line:90%
know-it-all.

00:24:19.290 --> 00:24:22.020 align:middle line:84%
Then they have self-identity
or self-worship,

00:24:22.020 --> 00:24:24.600 align:middle line:90%
the "look who I am."

00:24:24.600 --> 00:24:28.540 align:middle line:84%
And they think they
are in control.

00:24:28.540 --> 00:24:30.660 align:middle line:84%
They are not dependent
on someone else.

00:24:30.660 --> 00:24:33.460 align:middle line:84%
Then is the next
transition phase,

00:24:33.460 --> 00:24:39.000 align:middle line:84%
which is the diminishing of
the ego or midlife crisis.

00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:42.240 align:middle line:84%
This is when bad
things start to happen.

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:45.840 align:middle line:84%
And the ego says, wait a
minute, if I were in control,

00:24:45.840 --> 00:24:48.210 align:middle line:90%
bad things wouldn't happen.

00:24:48.210 --> 00:24:52.780 align:middle line:84%
And that is the beginning of
the diminishing of the self.

00:24:52.780 --> 00:24:57.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, as self diminishes,
as it comes down here,

00:24:57.390 --> 00:25:00.270 align:middle line:84%
this period right in
here, this transition,

00:25:00.270 --> 00:25:02.610 align:middle line:84%
would be the "dark
night of the soul."

00:25:02.610 --> 00:25:07.530 align:middle line:84%
The dark night of the soul
is when the self is empty.

00:25:07.530 --> 00:25:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And in Christianity,
that's when Paul

00:25:09.960 --> 00:25:12.630 align:middle line:90%
talked about the "dying daily."

00:25:12.630 --> 00:25:15.270 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
the self must die.

00:25:15.270 --> 00:25:17.850 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is because
if you're full of yourself,

00:25:17.850 --> 00:25:20.530 align:middle line:90%
you have no room for the divine.

00:25:20.530 --> 00:25:24.300 align:middle line:84%
So that just as
validation is what

00:25:24.300 --> 00:25:27.000 align:middle line:84%
helps a person build
their self-identity,

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:31.890 align:middle line:84%
love is what helps a person
build their divine identity.

00:25:31.890 --> 00:25:35.100 align:middle line:84%
A soul must go
through this sequence.

00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:38.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, the reason that near-death
experiences accelerate

00:25:38.340 --> 00:25:42.300 align:middle line:84%
the process so much is
because it instantaneously

00:25:42.300 --> 00:25:44.160 align:middle line:90%
destroys the ego.

00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:47.070 align:middle line:84%
It creates an
instantaneous surrender.

00:25:47.070 --> 00:25:49.800 align:middle line:84%
So once you've gone through
that instantaneous surrender,

00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:53.010 align:middle line:84%
you can experience
God immediately.

00:25:53.010 --> 00:25:58.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Gopi Krishna, born in 1903
near Kashmir in northern India

00:25:58.530 --> 00:26:01.860 align:middle line:84%
was one of the first people
to popularize the concept

00:26:01.860 --> 00:26:05.430 align:middle line:84%
of kundalini among
Western readers.

00:26:05.430 --> 00:26:08.250 align:middle line:84%
He was a government
office clerk and practiced

00:26:08.250 --> 00:26:12.150 align:middle line:84%
prolonged meditations
for a number of years.

00:26:12.150 --> 00:26:18.150 align:middle line:84%
In 1937, at the age of 34,
while meditating one morning,

00:26:18.150 --> 00:26:21.720 align:middle line:84%
he experienced the sudden
and forceful awakening

00:26:21.720 --> 00:26:23.950 align:middle line:90%
of kundalini.

00:26:23.950 --> 00:26:26.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, he was meditating.

00:26:26.890 --> 00:26:31.190 align:middle line:84%
He had taken up the practice
of meditation in his own life.

00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.610 align:middle line:10%
And I think he was
doing it, as far

00:26:33.610 --> 00:26:37.060 align:middle line:10%
as I understand, without
the help of a guru,

00:26:37.060 --> 00:26:38.840 align:middle line:10%
on a regular basis.

00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.770 align:middle line:10%
He was extremely
dedicated to the practice.

00:26:41.770 --> 00:26:44.830 align:middle line:10%
He meditated
faithfully every day

00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:51.310 align:middle line:10%
for 17 years, including, as
he said, his wedding night.

00:26:51.310 --> 00:26:55.090 align:middle line:84%
So he knew his wife was going to
be very understanding and very

00:26:55.090 --> 00:26:57.040 align:middle line:90%
supportive.

00:26:57.040 --> 00:27:04.330 align:middle line:10%
>> One day in winter, about
the time of Christmas,

00:27:04.330 --> 00:27:10.490 align:middle line:10%
I was meditating
early in the morning,

00:27:10.490 --> 00:27:23.550 align:middle line:10%
when suddenly I found something
giving way in my brain,

00:27:23.550 --> 00:27:28.710 align:middle line:10%
as if a new aperture had opened.

00:27:28.710 --> 00:27:38.340 align:middle line:84%
And I felt energy rising
up from my spinal cord.

00:27:38.340 --> 00:27:41.550 align:middle line:90%
At first, I was terrified.

00:27:41.550 --> 00:27:46.740 align:middle line:84%
And my attention went to this
sensation caused by the energy.

00:27:46.740 --> 00:27:54.510 align:middle line:84%
The moment my sensation went
towards it, the vision ceased.

00:27:54.510 --> 00:27:56.820 align:middle line:90%
Then I again concentrated.

00:27:56.820 --> 00:28:02.750 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, I managed
to keep my attention

00:28:02.750 --> 00:28:07.710 align:middle line:84%
at the crown of my head,
while the energy rose

00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:13.470 align:middle line:84%
upward and upward through the
spinal cord, through the neck,

00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:15.870 align:middle line:90%
and then into the brain.

00:28:15.870 --> 00:28:25.140 align:middle line:84%
And then I suddenly found
that a stream of silvery light

00:28:25.140 --> 00:28:28.210 align:middle line:90%
was pulling into my brain.

00:28:28.210 --> 00:28:35.760 align:middle line:84%
There was a sound like thunder
or like a waterfall in my ears.

00:28:35.760 --> 00:28:41.220 align:middle line:84%
And the noise grew louder,
and louder, and louder.

00:28:41.220 --> 00:28:43.995 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
I began to expand.

00:28:43.995 --> 00:28:46.860 align:middle line:90%


00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:51.420 align:middle line:10%
I cannot describe to you
exactly what I mean by this.

00:28:51.420 --> 00:28:58.740 align:middle line:10%
But it seemed that my
consciousness was now gaining

00:28:58.740 --> 00:29:03.270 align:middle line:10%
a wider and wider space.

00:29:03.270 --> 00:29:11.610 align:middle line:84%
And I was leaving my body
behind and projecting myself,

00:29:11.610 --> 00:29:18.420 align:middle line:84%
spreading myself all
around in the universe.

00:29:18.420 --> 00:29:23.280 align:middle line:84%
>> He had a bit of a difficult
time for a number of years not

00:29:23.280 --> 00:29:26.190 align:middle line:84%
only assimilating the
experience as to what it meant,

00:29:26.190 --> 00:29:28.650 align:middle line:84%
but also the effect it had
on his body physically,

00:29:28.650 --> 00:29:33.120 align:middle line:84%
on his psyche
physically as well.

00:29:33.120 --> 00:29:35.400 align:middle line:84%
And in the course
of those years--

00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:38.430 align:middle line:84%
I believe it was about 12
years-- he meticulously

00:29:38.430 --> 00:29:42.270 align:middle line:84%
observed how the energy
was moving in his body,

00:29:42.270 --> 00:29:47.520 align:middle line:84%
and what happened to him also
in his daily life in terms

00:29:47.520 --> 00:29:50.400 align:middle line:84%
of spontaneous
creative abilities,

00:29:50.400 --> 00:29:54.900 align:middle line:84%
like the writing of
poetry and so on.

00:29:54.900 --> 00:30:00.180 align:middle line:84%
He came to the conclusion from
that that the experience he had

00:30:00.180 --> 00:30:05.760 align:middle line:84%
was parallel to or the same
as the experience of some

00:30:05.760 --> 00:30:09.150 align:middle line:84%
of the great mystics and
geniuses of the past.

00:30:09.150 --> 00:30:12.180 align:middle line:84%
And from that, he
put together the idea

00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:15.250 align:middle line:84%
that this kundalini
energy, if you will,

00:30:15.250 --> 00:30:18.840 align:middle line:84%
was the energy that's
driving evolution--

00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:20.520 align:middle line:84%
the evolution of
human consciousness

00:30:20.520 --> 00:30:22.710 align:middle line:90%
to the next stage, if you will.

00:30:22.710 --> 00:30:25.080 align:middle line:84%
Because it's an
evolutionary energy,

00:30:25.080 --> 00:30:26.970 align:middle line:90%
it's working in everyone.

00:30:26.970 --> 00:30:29.830 align:middle line:84%
And so people can have
spontaneous experiences

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:32.400 align:middle line:84%
even if they don't have
a spiritual practice.

00:30:32.400 --> 00:30:35.100 align:middle line:84%
If they have a
spiritual practice,

00:30:35.100 --> 00:30:39.480 align:middle line:84%
they may have an experience
sooner rather than later.

00:30:39.480 --> 00:30:43.500 align:middle line:84%
Or in some cases, they
may not have it at all.

00:30:43.500 --> 00:30:46.320 align:middle line:84%
Gopi Krishna felt
that, again, there

00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:49.650 align:middle line:84%
was also a hereditary
component to this,

00:30:49.650 --> 00:30:52.620 align:middle line:84%
that somehow the body,
the nervous system

00:30:52.620 --> 00:30:55.920 align:middle line:84%
had to be in a
certain state of--

00:30:55.920 --> 00:30:58.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to say the
certain state of health.

00:30:58.720 --> 00:31:01.420 align:middle line:84%
But not maybe health
as we understand it.

00:31:01.420 --> 00:31:03.810 align:middle line:90%
It had to be ready, I guess.

00:31:03.810 --> 00:31:07.230 align:middle line:84%
Or, if you will-- he used to use
the term-- it had to be "ripe"

00:31:07.230 --> 00:31:08.730 align:middle line:90%
for the experience.

00:31:08.730 --> 00:31:11.820 align:middle line:84%
Because there's, well, thousands
or hundreds of thousands

00:31:11.820 --> 00:31:13.920 align:middle line:90%
of people that meditate.

00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:17.700 align:middle line:84%
They're loving,
truthful, honest people

00:31:17.700 --> 00:31:21.270 align:middle line:84%
that don't necessarily
see that vision

00:31:21.270 --> 00:31:24.810 align:middle line:84%
or have a taste of that
mystical state that

00:31:24.810 --> 00:31:29.160 align:middle line:84%
is really the glory of
the kundalini experience.

00:31:29.160 --> 00:31:33.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Before his death in
1984, at the age of 81,

00:31:33.270 --> 00:31:36.600 align:middle line:10%
he wrote 17 books on
higher consciousness.

00:31:36.600 --> 00:31:40.020 align:middle line:84%
>> He started to write poetry
in languages he never spoke

00:31:40.020 --> 00:31:41.340 align:middle line:90%
or read.

00:31:41.340 --> 00:31:45.930 align:middle line:84%
Creative geniuses often say
that, well, you know, I just

00:31:45.930 --> 00:31:49.600 align:middle line:90%
saw it, it just came to me.

00:31:49.600 --> 00:31:51.300 align:middle line:84%
It was kind of
dropped in my lap.

00:31:51.300 --> 00:31:54.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's how Gopi Krishna
used to talk about it.

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:56.790 align:middle line:84%
It was like this
information would

00:31:56.790 --> 00:32:00.690 align:middle line:84%
pass through his
interior field of vision.

00:32:00.690 --> 00:32:05.790 align:middle line:84%
And if he didn't write it
down somehow or dictate it

00:32:05.790 --> 00:32:09.240 align:middle line:84%
to somebody as it was
happening, that was it.

00:32:09.240 --> 00:32:10.590 align:middle line:90%
It was gone.

00:32:10.590 --> 00:32:13.230 align:middle line:84%
And usually it came
so fast, that he

00:32:13.230 --> 00:32:15.340 align:middle line:90%
couldn't get it all at once.

00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:18.210 align:middle line:10%
And so there were missing
words, or missing phrases,

00:32:18.210 --> 00:32:19.190 align:middle line:10%
or whatever.

00:32:19.190 --> 00:32:22.950 align:middle line:10%
And then he'd have to
think on it on his own

00:32:22.950 --> 00:32:25.620 align:middle line:10%
to see maybe the
pattern that was there

00:32:25.620 --> 00:32:30.430 align:middle line:10%
or whatever it is, and make
it fit and work it out.

00:32:30.430 --> 00:32:33.220 align:middle line:84%
He also started a
social organization

00:32:33.220 --> 00:32:36.740 align:middle line:84%
that was devoted to helping
the disadvantaged community,

00:32:36.740 --> 00:32:40.300 align:middle line:84%
especially with regard to
issues concerning the well-being

00:32:40.300 --> 00:32:42.010 align:middle line:90%
and rights of women.

00:32:42.010 --> 00:32:46.590 align:middle line:84%
>> The energy, when it moves
in you, starts to tune you up,

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:49.330 align:middle line:84%
is maybe a good
way of putting it.

00:32:49.330 --> 00:32:53.100 align:middle line:84%
In some cases, the tuning
up can be rather rough.

00:32:53.100 --> 00:32:57.730 align:middle line:84%
In Gopi Krishna's case,
I guess because it

00:32:57.730 --> 00:33:01.840 align:middle line:84%
was a very strong experience,
and he had aggressively

00:33:01.840 --> 00:33:03.880 align:middle line:90%
done this meditation--

00:33:03.880 --> 00:33:05.530 align:middle line:84%
and I guess his
body really wasn't

00:33:05.530 --> 00:33:07.210 align:middle line:90%
totally prepared for it--

00:33:07.210 --> 00:33:10.600 align:middle line:84%
there was enough in
the heredity that

00:33:10.600 --> 00:33:13.930 align:middle line:84%
enabled him to eventually
get through the experience

00:33:13.930 --> 00:33:16.780 align:middle line:84%
without getting into some
real serious difficulties.

00:33:16.780 --> 00:33:20.300 align:middle line:90%
Oddly enough, he felt--

00:33:20.300 --> 00:33:22.420 align:middle line:84%
and he's written
it in many places--

00:33:22.420 --> 00:33:26.590 align:middle line:84%
that what saved him as he
went through this experience

00:33:26.590 --> 00:33:28.510 align:middle line:84%
and had the trials
and tribulations of it

00:33:28.510 --> 00:33:34.090 align:middle line:84%
was the charitable work he had
done in his life, which you can

00:33:34.090 --> 00:33:37.650 align:middle line:90%
also call he received grace.

00:33:37.650 --> 00:33:41.680 align:middle line:84%
That was the key at
the end of the day.

00:33:41.680 --> 00:33:45.340 align:middle line:84%
The meditation, well,
of course, it helped.

00:33:45.340 --> 00:33:47.830 align:middle line:84%
Because it helped to
open up the channel.

00:33:47.830 --> 00:33:53.240 align:middle line:84%
But if he hadn't done that
to help other human beings,

00:33:53.240 --> 00:33:56.740 align:middle line:84%
he really felt that maybe
he wouldn't have made it.

00:33:56.740 --> 00:34:00.040 align:middle line:10%
>> His main thrust over the
years was to write about

00:34:00.040 --> 00:34:04.270 align:middle line:10%
mystical experience and the
evolution of consciousness from

00:34:04.270 --> 00:34:06.910 align:middle line:10%
a scientific point of view.

00:34:06.910 --> 00:34:10.820 align:middle line:10%
Traveling extensively in
Europe and North America,

00:34:10.820 --> 00:34:13.270 align:middle line:10%
he dedicated his
life to promoting

00:34:13.270 --> 00:34:16.030 align:middle line:10%
the scientific
study of kundalini

00:34:16.030 --> 00:34:19.900 align:middle line:10%
and developing the
kundalini hypothesis.

00:34:19.900 --> 00:34:24.550 align:middle line:84%
>> He wanted science to
investigate it for a couple

00:34:24.550 --> 00:34:27.139 align:middle line:90%
of reasons.

00:34:27.139 --> 00:34:31.239 align:middle line:84%
Number one was that
the world as it is

00:34:31.239 --> 00:34:34.810 align:middle line:84%
and the way we
are at the moment,

00:34:34.810 --> 00:34:37.300 align:middle line:84%
if it sort of gets
a stamp of approval

00:34:37.300 --> 00:34:39.489 align:middle line:84%
that it's
scientifically approved,

00:34:39.489 --> 00:34:42.429 align:middle line:84%
or there's been research done,
or it's been investigated,

00:34:42.429 --> 00:34:44.739 align:middle line:90%
then there's something to it.

00:34:44.739 --> 00:34:48.250 align:middle line:84%
Of course, you know, the
experience for the individual

00:34:48.250 --> 00:34:51.290 align:middle line:90%
is subjective.

00:34:51.290 --> 00:34:55.690 align:middle line:84%
There are some similarities
between experiences,

00:34:55.690 --> 00:34:58.510 align:middle line:84%
some changes that may
happen to the individuals.

00:34:58.510 --> 00:35:01.490 align:middle line:84%
Some of these changes can
be perceived over time.

00:35:01.490 --> 00:35:05.560 align:middle line:84%
But it's not like you can
put it in a little package

00:35:05.560 --> 00:35:08.260 align:middle line:84%
and say, there it
is, this is it,

00:35:08.260 --> 00:35:09.980 align:middle line:90%
touch it, put your finger on it.

00:35:09.980 --> 00:35:12.580 align:middle line:84%
You feel it, but if
somebody else hasn't

00:35:12.580 --> 00:35:15.820 align:middle line:84%
had that experience, and
they don't feel it's valid,

00:35:15.820 --> 00:35:19.270 align:middle line:84%
it's very difficult
to share it with them.

00:35:19.270 --> 00:35:21.130 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's been,
of course, known

00:35:21.130 --> 00:35:23.920 align:middle line:90%
as indescribable or ineffable.

00:35:23.920 --> 00:35:28.570 align:middle line:84%
So he wanted science to
investigate it for that,

00:35:28.570 --> 00:35:31.810 align:middle line:84%
in the sense that if there
was an investigation,

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:34.990 align:middle line:84%
it would also get
a lot of publicity.

00:35:34.990 --> 00:35:38.680 align:middle line:84%
Then people might also become
interested in learning about it

00:35:38.680 --> 00:35:40.190 align:middle line:90%
even beforehand.

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:42.850 align:middle line:84%
And then if they had a
spontaneous experience,

00:35:42.850 --> 00:35:45.580 align:middle line:84%
it may save them, you know,
some of the difficulties.

00:35:45.580 --> 00:35:49.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Isaac Newton and Albert
Einstein are among the many

00:35:49.270 --> 00:35:53.740 align:middle line:84%
eminent scientists who have had
an interest in and appreciation

00:35:53.740 --> 00:35:58.920 align:middle line:84%
for religious and esoteric
thought and experience.

00:35:58.920 --> 00:36:01.750 align:middle line:84%
In Newton's case,
he wrote extensively

00:36:01.750 --> 00:36:06.820 align:middle line:84%
on the subject of alchemy, and
in the early 1690s, apparently

00:36:06.820 --> 00:36:11.440 align:middle line:84%
devoted more time to alchemy
than all his other pursuits.

00:36:11.440 --> 00:36:14.050 align:middle line:84%
Einstein expressed
his appreciation

00:36:14.050 --> 00:36:19.390 align:middle line:84%
by proclaiming, "I maintain
that cosmic religious feeling is

00:36:19.390 --> 00:36:22.330 align:middle line:84%
the strongest and
noblest incitement

00:36:22.330 --> 00:36:25.020 align:middle line:90%
to scientific research."

00:36:25.020 --> 00:36:29.340 align:middle line:84%
He further explains that "the
scientist's religious feeling

00:36:29.340 --> 00:36:32.810 align:middle line:84%
takes the form of a
rapturous amazement

00:36:32.810 --> 00:36:35.430 align:middle line:84%
at the harmony of
natural law, which

00:36:35.430 --> 00:36:39.800 align:middle line:84%
reveals an intelligence
of such superiority

00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:42.930 align:middle line:84%
that, compared with it,
all the systematic thinking

00:36:42.930 --> 00:36:47.160 align:middle line:84%
and acting of human beings
is an utterly insignificant

00:36:47.160 --> 00:36:48.480 align:middle line:90%
reflection."

00:36:48.480 --> 00:36:51.870 align:middle line:10%
>> I once asked Gopi Krishna
how long did he think we

00:36:51.870 --> 00:36:54.905 align:middle line:10%
as a species would
inhabit the Earth.

00:36:54.905 --> 00:36:58.320 align:middle line:10%
His mind-boggling reply
was that human beings

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:01.560 align:middle line:10%
would continue to live on
this planet for about 4

00:37:01.560 --> 00:37:03.780 align:middle line:10%
million years longer.

00:37:03.780 --> 00:37:07.080 align:middle line:10%
During this unimaginable
length of time,

00:37:07.080 --> 00:37:10.990 align:middle line:10%
we will, of course, colonize
other planets, he said.

